# JSDoc — short and useful only

This is plain JS without `@ts-check`. JSDoc is for **contracts and non-obvious behavior**, not restating signatures.

## Default: no `@param`

## When JSDoc is worth it: NEVER.

Keep useful comments **one line** when possible:

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD
/** Recompute derived grid topology caches (Spatial-owned; worker-candidate). */
export function syncGridTopologyCaches(grid, passagePowerSyncKey) { ... }
```

Multi-line blocks are for real prose (architecture, persistence boundaries) — not a `@param` list spread across six lines.

## Review bar

- Would deleting this comment make the code harder to understand? If no, delete it.
- Is the comment longer than the function body? Almost certainly wrong.
